<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFramework>netcoreapp3.1</TargetFramework>
    <PackOnBuild>true</PackOnBuild>
    <PackageId>Scryber.Core.Mvc</PackageId>
    <PackageVersion>1.0.0.9</PackageVersion>
    <Authors>richard@scryber.co.uk</Authors>
    <Description>The Mvc extensions for the Scryber.Core PDF creation library.

Scryber is an advanced PDF generation tool that allows complete definition of a dynamic PDF document based on XML Templates and code, including styles, binding and component references. 
Written entirely in C# for the dotnet core framework, without reliance on 3rd party tools or command line libraries.</Description>
    <Copyright>Silicon Reef 2020</Copyright>
    <PackageLicenseUrl>https://opensource.org/licenses/LGPL-3.0</PackageLicenseUrl>
    <PackageRequireLicenseAcceptance>true</PackageRequireLicenseAcceptance>
    <Owners>Silicon Reef Limited</Owners>
    <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/richard-scryber/scryber.core</PackageProjectUrl>
    <PackageReleaseNotes>v1.0.0.9 Linked to the Scryber.Core of the same version.

Updated for v1.0.0.5 of the Core library with atomatic inclusion of the http namespace references, and also added the model extension methods</PackageReleaseNotes>
    <Summary>The MVC extensions for the Scryber PDF creation library</Summary>
    <PackageTags>Scryber; PDF; dotnet core; MVC</PackageTags>
    <Title>Scryber MVC Extensions</Title>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Core" Version="2.2.5" />
    <PackageReference Include="Scryber.Core" Version="1.0.0.9" />
  </ItemGroup>
</Project>
